<span id="freeTextContainer677903925157838800">Although I also enjoyed the earlier books in the series, this one blew me away the first time I read it. I loved the puzzles and historical connections. If I recall, this was her most complex plot yet, and in my opinion truly manifested her talent as a writer. As I&apos;ve gotten older, I still really love this book and enjoy rereading it. Although I am more aware of its flaws and typos, they aren&apos;t enough to significantly detract from enjoyment of the book.</span>
  <span id="freeText677903925157838800" style="display:none">Although I also enjoyed the earlier books in the series, this one blew me away the first time I read it. I loved the puzzles and historical connections. If I recall, this was her most complex plot yet, and in my opinion truly manifested her talent as a writer. As I've gotten older, I still really love this book and enjoy rereading it. Although I am more aware of its flaws and typos, they aren't enough to significantly detract from enjoyment of the book.</span>
